                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d887">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M)/391: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kelley</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-09-30T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >September 30, 1940—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>73. Your 107, September 28, noon. Department immediately asking Embassy in London
                    to inaugurate discussions looking towards agreement with British Government.
                    Please give as full as possible information regarding (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>)
                    amount of chrome by grades in stock in Turkey now, (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>)
                    prospective schedule of production under the agreement with Great Britain, (<hi
                        rend="italic">c</hi>) any other prospective production in Turkey.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
